review_blob: Bottle. Opaque pour with a foamy brown head. Nose is cocoa, booze, caramel. Flavor is like semisweet dark chocolate, milk. Earthy and boozy. Great smooth mouthfeel. Dry finish. Enjoyed this one.

Bottle picked up during a visit to Rochester. Pours a clear copper color with a small white head; nose is tropical fruit, hops, pine. Flavor follows with decent balance. Bitter finish. Certainly not on par with west coast triple IPAs, but decent.
beer_name: Three Heads Tre Kind Triple IPA

review_blob: Draft at Brodys. Hazy golden pour with a medium head. Nose is fruit, funk. Flavor follows with a tart finish. Very fresh, enjoyable, even though its not my preferred style.
Picked one up in Oahu, thinking it was brewed in Hawaii. Pours a cloudy yellow color with a small head. Nose is wheat and not much else. Flavor is light, not really a true hef; watery/thin.
Bomber picked up in Oahu. Pours a dark golden color with medium head. Nose is hops, citrus; flavor follows with some floral and caramel notes; malt, bread. Sweet flavor with a bitter finish. Ok.
Guest tap at Brodys in Jamul. Black pour with a medium beige head. Nose is roast, chocolate, malt, bread. Flavor follows with some ash and coffee. Thin to medium mouthfeel.
beer_name: Alpine Beer Company Ryeder on the Storm

review_blob: Bottle poured into a pint glass. Golden pour with a medium white head, and a fantastic citrus aroma. Flavor is sweet malt and a zesty citrus flavor. Bitter finish. Definitely better than Grapefruit Sculpin.

On tap at Brodys. Pours a clear golden color with small white head. Nose dank and hoppy with tropical fruit. Flavor follows with hops, fruity, and a bitter finish. Maybe its because I tasted this back to back with fantastic HFS and Nelson, but I thought it was a B+... which is better than most beers out there!

Handed out for free, on tap, at Alpine night at Brodys. Hazy orange pour with a small white head. Nose is definitely tangerine. Flavor follows with some mild hop notes, bitter, and a disappointing finish. Just ok.
beer_name: Green Flash Tangerine Soul Style IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Pours jet black with a medium head with good retention. Flavor is coffee, chocolate, oats. Really good mouthfeel; tastes like bitter chocolate, malt, oats. Straightforward and pretty enjoyable.
beer_name: Stone 20th Anniversary Encore Series: Bitter Chocolate Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: On tap at Moviehouse Flower Mound while I was visiting Dallas for a meeting. Pours a dark brown, clear color. Not much nose, mostly malt. Flavor is nutty, chocolate, malt; no pecan really. Thin mouthfeel. Pretty average porter.
On tap at Brodys. Clear yellow with a smallish head. Nose is tropical fruit, pine; flavor follows with great hop flavors as well as medium malt. Crisp finish. Very good; reminded me a lot of Grunion.

Bottle picked up in Oahu. Pours a yellow/copper color, clear with medium head. Nose is citrus, tropical fruit/pineapple, grapefruit. Flavor is sweet, with citrus, malt, and a tropical/piney finish. Medium body. Would buy again.

Bottle to snifter. Pours a dark brown/red color with a medium beige head. Nose is bourbon and caramel. Flavor follows with vanilla, bread, oak/wood, raisin. Somewhat thin on the mouthfeel. Definitely a unique beer; probably wouldnt buy another though.
Bottle. Pours black and has a small head. Nose is chocolate, bourbon/booze, malt. Flavor follows with some roast and an interesting and unique salty back end. Full mouthfeel. Very good.
This was on tap at Brodys. Pours a ruby/brown color with minimal head. Nose is booze and cinnamon. Flavor follows - wood, cinnamon, booze. Somewhat thin. Reminded me of Hunaphu.
beer_name: Oskar Blues Ten Fidy - Heaven Hill

review_blob: Growler. Hazy yellow pour with a big head that lasts. Nose is strong floral, pine, malt. Flavor is pine with some malt and bread. Dry, bitter finish. Still an excellent beer from Alpine but not as great as some of their IPAs.
beer_name: Alpine Beer Company Pub Cat Ale

review_blob: Growler. Pours a clear golden color with a medium white head. Hose is citrusy hops. Flavor follows with some tropical notes and a good malt balance. Bitter finish. Clean, crisp, fresh, really good.
Bottle to tulip. Pours motor oil black with a small head. Nose is chocolate, coffee, malt, wood. Flavor follows perfectly. Full-bodied, nice mouthfeel, bitter finish. This is what a stout should be.

Draft at the brewpub, right after the Chargers/Packers game. Orange pour with a white head. Nose is citrus/floral, with some garlic notes. Medium body, sweet malt backbone with floral, grapefruit, orange notes. This was right up my alley; reminded me a lot of Grunion from Ballast Point.

So, this won gold at GABF but it has only 3 ratings?! On tap at Brodys. Golden pour with a medium white head. Nose is good: citrus, tropical fruit, hops. Flavor is malty with some tropical notes, with a hoppy bitter finish. Solid, clean and refreshing, but not unique.
Growler to tulip. Pours an amber color with a medium off white head. Nose is really great - pine, citrus, hops, malt, toffee. Flavor is pine, citrus, and sweet malt, with a dry slightly hoppy finish.
Growler. Orange/pale clear pour with white head. Nose is citra/orange with some floral and peach. Flavor is Citra, Mosaic, citrus peach and some tropical/mango. Bitter finish.

Bottle shared with friends. Black pour with a small brown head. Nose is vanilla, marshmallow, malt. Flavor follows with primarily a sweet marshmallow taste. Nice barrel finish with some rye booze heat at the end. Fantastic beer.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Vanilla Rye Barrel

review_blob: On tap at the brewery. Pours a dark brown color with almost no head; looks like BA Speedway. Nose is fantastic: toffee, chocolate, coffee. Flavor strikes me most like BA Wee Heavy at first: toffee, caramel, vanilla, raisin, booze. Great, full smooth body. Finishes with some coffee notes. Amazing that they pulled off a great beer by blending 3.

Poured from a growler shared by Steve. Black pour with a small head. Nose is hops mixed with malt/chocolate. Flavor is toasted malt, chocolate, with a hoppy finish. Definitely different. Flavors dont go together great.

Bottle. Pours a clear caramel color with a small cream head. Nose is orange, caramel, wood, alcohol. Flavor follows with some cinnamon, tartness, malt, brown sugar. Kinda thin, but boozy. Tastes similar to the Bruery anniversary beers, but not as well rounded/complex.

Bomber picked up in Costco. Pours a gold/copper color, clear, with a small head. Nose is great - citrus, herbs, hops. Flavor follows with some sweetness, grass and a medium malty finish. Decent but I probably wouldnt seek it out again.

Had this on tap at GABF, and again at Brodys in San Diego. Pours a hazy orange color, with a tropical fruit nose. Flavor is just great - tropical fruits, pineapple, mango, all mosaic. Finishes slightly dank. Bear Republic needs to bottle this!

Bottle poured into a tulip. Pours a dark brown with a fizziness that causes the small head to disappear quickly. Nose is nice - booze, vanilla, sugar. Flavor is a lot like Melange 3; very sweet, caramel, hazelnut, with additional marshmallow and vanilla, and a boozy finish. Really good.
UPDATED: SEP 3, 2015
Bottle. Pours a dark cola color with the scent of spice and citrus. Flavor is wild - cola, malt, spice. Does taste like coke on the back end. This is really unique but Im not sure Id drink it again.
On tap at the Bruery. Clear golden pour with a small white head. Nose is a mix of sweet and hoppy bitter. Flavor is clean - citrus, grass, yeast, bitter finish. Solid.
Poured into a pint glass. Golden hazy pour with aroma of spices, clove. Flavor follows with a bitter finish. Decent for a warm afternoon.

Bottle, tried while visiting the Grand Tetons. Hazy gold pour with small white head. Nose is German yeast, banana, clove. Flavor follows, with medium body and light spiciness. Good beer for a warm afternoon in Wyoming.
beer_name: Grand Teton Howling Wolf Weisse Bier

review_blob: Can to pint glass. Black pour with small tan head. Nose is big - coffee, ash, chocolate. Flavor follows with a bitter finish. Slightly thin, but very good; I can see why these guys win a lot of GABF medals.
On tap at the brewpub. Pours dark brown/black, with a big fluffy head. Nose is roast, ash; flavor follows with bitter chocolate. Great full mouthfeel.
beer_name: Snow Eagle Dark Horse Milk Stout

review_blob: On tap; too bad they dont bottle this. Hazy yellow pour with a medium head. Nose is pine, hops. Flavor is sweet malt, with a pine/hoppy finish. Nice, smooth mouthfeel. Impressed with this one.
On tap at their brewpub. Pours clear golden with a off-white head. Aroma is malt, caramel, pine and grassy hops. Taste is sweet with light hops. Medium bodied. Pretty average.
They call this an IPA? I had it on tap in Yellowstone. It pours an amber color with a white head. Nose is caramel, hops, tropical fruit. Flavor is caramel/grain; no hops. Light bodied.

On tap up in Lake Tahoe. Pours hazy yellow with a big white head. Nose is hops, pine, and citrus. Flavor is hop forward with citrus and only mild bitterness and not much malt. Very good west coast style IPA.
Poured from a growler. Copper pour, medium head. Citrus aroma with lingering hops. Floral, citrus flavor; nice bitter finish. Fantastic DIPA.
beer_name: Arizona Wilderness DC Mountain Double IPA

review_blob: Can. Pours a hazy amber with a medium white head. Nose is citrus and hops. Flavor is more bitter and piney and less malty. Solid but not unique.

Can. Pours a hazy amber orange color with lots of murky citrus pith visible. Nose is big citrus, mostly orange/tangerine. Flavor follows with grapefruit and pineapple. Hoppy finish with slight malt. I drank this all week in Hawaii, and thought it was a pretty awesome beer for the occasion, though unlike any DIPA Ive ever tried. Plus, drinking this helps raise money for shark research. Pretty damn awesome.
beer_name: Maui Brewing Lorenzini Double IPA (6th Sense)

review_blob: 2014 bottle. Pours black with a small brown head that disappears quickly. Nose is vanilla, bourbon, wood, coffee. Flavor follows; gets better as the beer warms. Creamy full mouthfeel and very well balanced. Awesome beer.
Bottle. Dark brown pour, tan head. Nose is malt, bourbon, chocolate. Flavor follows with some oak and roast. Sticky full mouthfeel. Very good.

Bottle. Pours dark black. Nose is coconut and cinnamon, booze. Flavor is a cinnamon explosion; cant even taste the booze or the coconut in there. Very little resemblance to regular bourbon county. And the finish? Cinnamon, too. Off balance and definitely over-hyped.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Proprietors 2014

review_blob: Bomber. Pours gold/orange with white head. Nose is hops, pine, and a little malt. Flavor is pithy bitter, dank, resin, with light malt. Medium body, bitter finish.

Bottle from a trade. Amber pour with a small head. Nose is grapefruit, tropical mango; flavor follows with sweet malt and a slightly bitter finish. Good balance. I thought this was very solid, compared to most Canadian IPAs Ive tried so far.
On tap at Brodys. Nose is great, very citrusy, but the appearance is a pale yellow color that looks like a light beer. Flavor is one dimensional, with lemon/citrus and light malt. Dry finish.
beer_name: Ballast Point / Coedo East to West IPA
